  "title": "Designing REST APIs using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides an overview of creating REST APIs using the FastAPI framework in Python 3.12+. FastAPI is a modern, high-performance web framework that simplifies API development through its intuitive syntax and built-in features.",
  "key_points": [
    "FastAPI offers automatic documentation generation",
    "Supports OpenAPI/Swagger specifications for easy integration with other tools",
    "Built on top of Starlette, a high-performance web framework for ASGI",
    "Includes type hints and static type checking for better code readability",
    "Provides a flexible routing system that supports path parameters, query parameters, and cookies"
  ],
